{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb8e9094c-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s8343a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8343a"},"text":"§ 8343a.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Alternative forms of annuities","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8e9094d-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s8343a/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Office of Personnel Management shall prescribe regulations under which any employee or Member who has a life-threatening affliction or other critical medical condition may, at the time of retiring under this subchapter (other than under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s8337"},"text":"section 8337 of this title","children":[],"tail":"), elect annuity benefits under this section instead of any other benefits under this subchapter (including any benefits under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s8341"},"text":"section 8341 of this title","children":[],"tail":") based on the service of the employee or Member."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8e9094e-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s8343a/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" Subject to subsection (c), the Office shall by regulation provide for such alternative forms of annuities as the Office considers appropriate, except that among the alternatives offered shall be—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8e9094f-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s8343a/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" an alternative which provides for—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8e90950-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s8343a/b/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" payment of the lump-sum credit to the employee or Member; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8e90951-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s8343a/b/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" payment of an annuity to the employee or Member for life; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8e90952-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s8343a/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of an employee or Member who is married at the time of retirement, an alternative which provides for—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8e90953-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s8343a/b/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" payment of the lump-sum credit to the employee or Member; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8e90954-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s8343a/b/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" payment of an annuity to the employee or Member for life, with a survivor annuity payable for the life of a surviving spouse.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8e90955-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s8343a/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Each alternative provided for under subsection (b) shall, to the extent practicable, be designed such that the present value of the benefits provided under such alternative (including any lump-sum credit) is actuarially equivalent to the present value of the annuity which would otherwise be provided the employee or Member under this subchapter, as computed under subsections (a)–(i), (n), (q), (r), and (s) of section 8339.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8e90956-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s8343a/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" An employee or Member who, at the time of retiring under this subchapter—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8e90957-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s8343a/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is married, shall be ineligible to make an election under this section unless a waiver is made under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s8339/j/1"},"text":"section 8339(j)(1) of this title","children":[],"tail":"; or"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8e90958-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s8343a/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" has a former spouse, shall be ineligible to make an election under this section if the former spouse is entitled to benefits under section 8341(h) or 8345(j) of this title (based on the service of the employee or Member) under the terms of a decree of divorce or annulment, or a court order or court-approved property settlement incident to any such decree, with respect to which the Office has been duly notified.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8e90959-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s8343a/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" An employee or Member who is married at the time of retiring under this subchapter and who makes an election under this section may, during the 18-month period beginning on the date of retirement, make the election provided for under section 8339(","children":[{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"o","children":[],"tail":") of this title, subject to the deposit requirement thereunder."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb8e9095a-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/335/tII/s204/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–335, title II, § 204(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-06-06"},"text":"June 6, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/591"},"text":"100 Stat. 591","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/428/s2/d/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–428, § 2(d)(5)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-10-15"},"text":"Oct. 15, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/929"},"text":"104 Stat. 929","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/508/tVII/s7001/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–508, title VII, § 7001(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-05"},"text":"Nov. 5, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/1388-327"},"text":"104 Stat. 1388–327","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/66/tXI/s11002/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–66, title XI, § 11002(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-08-10"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1993","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/107/409"},"text":"107 Stat. 409","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/61/tV/s516/a/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–61, title V, § 516(a)(5)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-10-10"},"text":"Oct. 10, 1997","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/111/1306"},"text":"111 Stat. 1306","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/553/s1/a/2/tIII/s308/h/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–553, § 1(a)(2) [title III, § 308(h)(5)]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-12-21"},"text":"Dec. 21, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/2762"},"text":"114 Stat. 2762","children":[],"tail":", 2762A–89.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb8e9095b-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb8e9095c-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb8e9095d-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2000—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/553"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–553","children":[],"tail":" substituted “(a)–(i), (n), (q), (r), and (s)” for “(a)–(i), (n), (q), and (r)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1997—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/61"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–61","children":[],"tail":", which directed the substitution of “(q), and (r) of section 8339” for “and (q) of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s8339"},"text":"section 8339 of this title","children":[],"tail":"” in section 8334a(c), was executed by making the substitution in subsec. (c) of this section to reflect the probable intent of Congress, because there is no section 8334a in this title."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1993—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/66/s11002/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–66, § 11002(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “any employee or Member who has a life-threatening affliction or other critical medical condition” for “an employee or Member”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/66/s11002/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–66, § 11002(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", struck out subsec. (f) which prohibited election of alternative form of annuity where commencement date would be after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-12-01"},"text":"Dec. 1, 1990","children":[],"tail":", with certain exceptions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1990—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/428"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–428","children":[],"tail":" substituted “(a)–(i), (n), and (q)” for “(a)–(i) and (n)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/508"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–508","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (f)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb8e9095e-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idb8e9095f-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2000 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/553"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–553","children":[],"tail":" effective on the first day of the first applicable pay period that begins on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-12-21"},"text":"Dec. 21, 2000","children":[],"tail":", and applicable only to an individual who is employed as a member of the Supreme Court Police after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-12-21"},"text":"Dec. 21, 2000","children":[],"tail":", see section 1(a)(2) [title III, § 308(i), (j)] of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/553"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–553","children":[],"tail":", set out in a Supreme Court Police Retirement note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s8331"},"text":"section 8331 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idb8e90960-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1997 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/61"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–61","children":[],"tail":" applicable to any annuity commencing before, on, or after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-10-10"},"text":"Oct. 10, 1997","children":[],"tail":", and effective with regard to any payment made after the first month following "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-10-10"},"text":"Oct. 10, 1997","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/61/s516/b"},"text":"section 516(b) of Pub. L. 105–61","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s8334"},"text":"section 8334 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idb8e90961-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1993 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/66/s11002/d"},"text":"Section 11002(d) of Pub. L. 103–66","children":[],"tail":" provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/103/66/s11002/d"},"text":"“The amendments made by this section [amending this section and ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s8420a"},"text":"section 8420a of this title","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s4047"},"text":"section 4047 of Title 22","children":[],"tail":", Foreign Relations and Intercourse, and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s2143"},"text":"section 2143 of Title 50","children":[],"tail":", War and National Defense] shall become effective on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-01"},"text":"October 1, 1994","children":[],"tail":", and shall apply with respect to any annuity commencing on or after that date.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"idb8e90962-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section effective ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-06-06"},"text":"June 6, 1986","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/335/s702/b/3"},"text":"section 702(b)(3) of Pub. L. 99–335","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s8401"},"text":"section 8401 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idb8e90963-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Applicability of Sections 8343a(f) and 8420a(f) to Individuals Called to or Performing Duty in Connection With Operation Desert Shield","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/508/s7001/a/4"},"text":"Section 7001(a)(4) of Pub. L. 101–508","children":[],"tail":" provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/101/508/s7001/a/4"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"“(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In applying the provisions of section 8343a(f) or 8420a(f) of title 5, United States Code (as amended by paragraph (1)) to any individual described in subparagraph (B), the reference in such provisions to ‘","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-12-01"},"text":"December 1, 1990","children":[],"tail":"’ shall be deemed to read ‘"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-12-01"},"text":"December 1, 1991","children":[],"tail":"’."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"“(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" This paragraph applies with respect to any individual who—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"“(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subclause","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"I"},"text":"(I)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is a member of the Armed Forces of the United States who, before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-12-01"},"text":"December 1, 1990","children":[],"tail":", was called or ordered to active duty (other than for training) pursuant to section 672 [now 12301], 673 [now 12302], 673b [now 12304], 674 [now 12306], 675 [now 12307], or 688 of title 10, United States Code, in connection with Operation Desert Shield; or"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subclause","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"II"},"text":"“(II)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is an employee of the Department of Defense who is certified by the Secretary of Defense to have performed, after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-30"},"text":"November 30, 1990","children":[],"tail":", duties essential for the support of Operation Desert Shield; and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"“(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" would have been eligible to make an election under section 8343a or 8420a of title 5, United States Code (as amended by paragraph (1)) as of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-30"},"text":"November 30, 1990","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"“(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Office of Personnel Management may prescribe such regulations as may be necessary to carry out this paragraph.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idb8e90964-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Partial Deferred Payment of Lump-Sum Credit for Certain Individuals Electing Alternative Forms of Annuities","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/239/tIV/s4005"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–239, title IV, § 4005","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 1989","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/103/2135"},"text":"103 Stat. 2135","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/508/tVII/s7001/a/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–508, title VII, § 7001(a)(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":"–(C)(i), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-05"},"text":"Nov. 5, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/1388-328"},"text":"104 Stat. 1388–328","children":[],"tail":", provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/101/508/tVII/s7001/a/2/A"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"“(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In General","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding any other provision of law, and except as provided in subsection (c), any lump-sum credit payable to an employee or Member pursuant to the election of an alternative form of annuity by such employee or Member under section 8343a or ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s8420a"},"text":"section 8420a of title 5","children":[],"tail":", United States Code, shall be paid in accordance with the schedule under subsection (b) (instead of the schedule which would otherwise apply), if the commencement date of the annuity payable to such employee or Member occurs after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-12-02"},"text":"December 2, 1989","children":[],"tail":", and before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-12-02"},"text":"December 2, 1990","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"“(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Schedule of Payments","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The schedule of payment of any lump-sum credit subject to this section is as follows:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" 50 percent of the lump-sum credit shall be payable on the date on which, but for the enactment of this section, the full amount of the lump-sum credit would otherwise be payable.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The remainder of the lump-sum credit shall be payable on the date which occurs 12 months after the date on which the payment described in paragraph (1) is paid.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"An amount payable in accordance with paragraph (2) shall be payable with interest, computed using the rate under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s8334/e/3"},"text":"section 8334(e)(3) of title 5","children":[],"tail":", United States Code."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"“(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Exceptions","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Office of Personnel Management shall prescribe regulations to provide that, unless the individual involved indicates otherwise by written notice to the Office (submitted at such time and in such manner as the regulations may require), this section shall not apply—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of any individual who is separated from Government service involuntarily, other than for cause on charges of misconduct or delinquency; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of any individual as to whom the application of this section would be against equity and good conscience, due to a life-threatening affliction or other critical medical condition affecting such individual.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"“(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Annuity Benefits Not Affected","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Nothing in this section shall affect the commencement date, the amount, or any other aspect of any annuity benefits payable under section 8343a or ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s8420a"},"text":"section 8420a of title 5","children":[],"tail":", United States Code."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"“(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Definitions","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of this section, the terms ‘lump-sum credit’, ‘employee’, and ‘Member’ each has the meaning given such term by section 8331 or ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s8401"},"text":"section 8401 of title 5","children":[],"tail":", United States Code, as appropriate."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"“(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Continued Applicability","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The preceding provisions of this section (disregarding the provision in subsection (a) limiting this section’s applicability to annuities commencing before the date specified in such provision) shall also apply in the case of any employee or Member whose election of an alternative form of annuity would not have been allowable under section 8343a(f) or 8420a(f) of title 5, United States Code (as the case may be), but for—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" paragraph (2)(A) thereof; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" section 7001(a)(4) of the Omnibus Budget Reconciliation Act of 1990 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/508"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–508","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note above].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"[","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/508/s7001/a/2/C/ii"},"text":"Section 7001(a)(2)(C)(ii) of Pub. L. 101–508","children":[],"tail":" provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/101/508/s7001/a/2/C/ii"},"text":"“The amendments made by clause (i) [amending ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/239/s4005"},"text":"section 4005 of Pub. L. 101–239","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/203/s6001"},"text":"section 6001 of Pub. L. 100–203","children":[],"tail":", set out as notes above and below] shall not apply in any case in which the first half of the lump-sum payment involved was paid before the beginning of the 11-month period which ends on the date of the enactment of this Act ["},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-05"},"text":"Nov. 5, 1990","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n]"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Similar provisions were contained in the following acts:","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/227/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–227, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-12-12"},"text":"Dec. 12, 1989","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/103/1943"},"text":"103 Stat. 1943","children":[],"tail":", which was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/508/tVII/s7001/a/2/D"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–508, title VII, § 7001(a)(2)(D)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-05"},"text":"Nov. 5, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/1388-328"},"text":"104 Stat. 1388–328","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/203/tVI/s6001"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–203, title VI, § 6001","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-12-22"},"text":"Dec. 22, 1987","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/101/1330-275"},"text":"101 Stat. 1330–275","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/103/s6"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–103, § 6","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-09-30"},"text":"Sept. 30, 1989","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/103/672"},"text":"103 Stat. 672","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/508/tVII/s7001/a/2/C/i"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–508, title VII, § 7001(a)(2)(C)(i)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-05"},"text":"Nov. 5, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/1388-328"},"text":"104 Stat. 1388–328","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
